Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Digital Farm Management Portal for Biosecurity in Pig and Poultry Farms

1. Executive Summary
1.1 Product Overview
The Digital Farm Management Portal is a comprehensive web and mobile platform designed to empower pig and poultry farmers with practical biosecurity tools, education, and compliance tracking capabilities. The platform addresses the critical gap in accessible biosecurity information and management tools, particularly for smallholder farmers in resource-limited areas.
1.2 Vision Statement
To become the definitive digital platform for farm-level biosecurity management in the pig and poultry sectors, preventing disease outbreaks, protecting livelihoods, and strengthening food security through accessible technology and actionable insights.
1.3 Success Metrics

User Adoption: 50,000+ registered farmers within first 18 months
Engagement: 70% monthly active user rate among registered farmers
Compliance: 60% of farms achieving baseline biosecurity compliance within 12 months
Disease Prevention: Measurable reduction in disease outbreak incidents in participating farms
User Satisfaction: Net Promoter Score (NPS) > 40


2. Problem Statement
2.1 Current Challenges
Farmers, especially smallholders, face multiple barriers to implementing effective biosecurity:

Limited access to practical, localized biosecurity information
Lack of affordable risk assessment and monitoring tools
Difficulty understanding and tracking regulatory compliance requirements
Delayed awareness of disease outbreaks in their region
Insufficient technical support and training resources
Poor digital record-keeping leading to compliance gaps
Language and literacy barriers to accessing technical information

2.2 Impact of Inaction
Without intervention, the livestock sector faces:

Continued economic losses from preventable disease outbreaks
Threats to food security and rural livelihoods
Regulatory non-compliance and market access restrictions
Limited data for evidence-based policy making
Perpetuation of biosecurity knowledge gaps


3. Target Users
3.1 Primary Users
Smallholder Farmers

Profile: Small to medium-scale pig/poultry farmers (10-1000 birds/animals)
Needs: Simple, actionable biosecurity guidance; low-cost solutions; local language support
Tech Proficiency: Basic smartphone usage; limited internet connectivity
Pain Points: Resource constraints, limited technical knowledge, compliance complexity

Commercial Farm Operators

Profile: Large-scale operations (1000+ animals)
Needs: Advanced analytics, compliance documentation, staff training tools
Tech Proficiency: Moderate to high; regular internet access
Pain Points: Complex compliance requirements, staff training consistency, audit preparation

3.2 Secondary Users
Veterinarians

Role: Provide technical guidance and farm audits
Needs: Access to farm records, risk assessment data, training content
Value: Remote monitoring capabilities, standardized assessment tools

Extension Workers

Role: Field-level support and farmer education
Needs: Training materials, farmer progress tracking, field data collection tools
Value: Scalable outreach, impact measurement

Regulatory Authorities

Role: Policy making, surveillance, compliance monitoring
Needs: Aggregated data, trend analysis, compliance dashboards
Value: Data-driven decision making, outbreak prediction, regulatory effectiveness measurement

Agricultural Input Suppliers

Role: Provide biosecurity products and services
Needs: Market intelligence, farmer connection
Value: Targeted marketing, demand forecasting


4. User Stories
4.1 Farmer Stories
As a smallholder poultry farmer, I want to receive disease outbreak alerts in my local language so that I can take immediate protective measures for my flock.
As a pig farmer, I want to complete a simple biosecurity risk assessment so that I can identify and address vulnerabilities on my farm.
As a new farmer, I want step-by-step video tutorials on biosecurity practices so that I can implement proper protocols without expensive consultants.
As a commercial farm operator, I want to track compliance requirements and deadlines so that I can maintain disease-free compartment certification.
As a farmer with limited literacy, I want voice-based instructions and visual guides so that I can access information without reading lengthy documents.
4.2 Veterinarian Stories
As a veterinarian, I want to review my clients' farm records remotely so that I can provide targeted advice without always visiting in person.
As a veterinary officer, I want to see aggregated risk scores for farms in my area so that I can prioritize support visits effectively.
4.3 Authority Stories
As a disease surveillance officer, I want real-time visibility into biosecurity practices across regions so that I can identify high-risk areas requiring intervention.
As a policy maker, I want to analyze trends in farmer compliance and disease incidence so that I can develop evidence-based regulations and support programs.

5. Product Features & Requirements
5.1 Core Features
5.1.1 Customizable Risk Assessment Tool
Priority: P0 (Must Have)
Description: Interactive questionnaire-based tool that evaluates farm-level biosecurity risks based on local epidemiological conditions, farm type, size, and practices.
Functional Requirements:

Support for both pig and poultry farm types with species-specific questions
Dynamic questionnaire that adapts based on previous answers
Risk scoring algorithm with categorization (Low, Medium, High, Critical)
Localized risk factors based on geographic region and disease prevalence
Visual risk dashboard showing scores across different biosecurity domains:

Farm location and design
Animal sourcing and movement
Feed and water management
Personnel and visitor protocols
Waste management and sanitation
Disease monitoring and response


Historical risk tracking to show improvement over time
Ability to save and resume assessments
Offline capability for areas with poor connectivity

Technical Requirements:

Maximum assessment completion time: 15 minutes
Support for 10+ regional languages
Work on devices with limited storage (< 500MB app size)
Sync data when connection becomes available

Acceptance Criteria:

Farmer can complete risk assessment in their preferred language
System generates actionable recommendations based on risk score
Assessment results are saved and accessible for future reference
Farmers can retake assessments quarterly to track improvements


5.1.2 Interactive Training Modules
Priority: P0 (Must Have)
Description: Comprehensive educational content library covering biosecurity best practices, delivered through multiple formats to accommodate different learning styles and literacy levels.
Functional Requirements:

Content Types:

Video tutorials (2-5 minutes each) with subtitles
Animated infographics and visual guides
Audio lessons in local languages
Interactive quizzes and knowledge checks
Downloadable PDF guides and checklists
Case studies and success stories from local farmers


Content Organization:

Beginner, intermediate, and advanced levels
Topic-based modules (disease prevention, sanitation, nutrition, etc.)
Species-specific tracks (pig vs. poultry)
Seasonal content (monsoon protocols, heat stress management)


Learning Features:

Progress tracking and completion certificates
Bookmarking and favorites
Search functionality
Recommended content based on risk assessment results
Community discussion forums per module


Accessibility:

Low-bandwidth video streaming options
Download for offline viewing
Text-to-speech for written content
High-contrast mode for visually impaired users



Technical Requirements:

Video streaming optimized for 2G/3G networks
Content caching for offline access
Maximum video file size: 20MB per module
Support for at least 8 regional languages

Acceptance Criteria:

50+ training modules available at launch
Farmers can complete modules offline
Progress is saved and synced across devices
Farmers receive certificates upon module completion


