6. Technical Architecture
6.1 System Architecture
Architecture Pattern: Microservices-based, cloud-native architecture
Core Components:

Frontend: Progressive Web App (PWA) + Native Android App
Backend: Node.js/Python microservices
Database: PostgreSQL (relational), MongoDB (document), Redis (caching)
Storage: Cloud object storage for media and documents
Message Queue: RabbitMQ/Apache Kafka for async processing
Search: Elasticsearch for content and farm search
Analytics: Data warehouse (BigQuery/Redshift) with BI tools

6.2 Technology Stack
Frontend:

React.js with Next.js for PWA
React Native for Android native app
TailwindCSS for responsive design
Redux for state management
Service Workers for offline functionality

Backend:

Node.js with Express.js for API services
Python with FastAPI for AI/ML services
GraphQL for flexible data querying
WebSocket for real-time notifications

Database:

PostgreSQL for transactional data
MongoDB for unstructured farm records
Redis for session management and caching
TimescaleDB for time-series IoT data

Infrastructure:

Cloud Platform: AWS/Google Cloud/Azure
Container Orchestration: Kubernetes
CI/CD: GitHub Actions/GitLab CI
Monitoring: Prometheus + Grafana
Logging: ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)

6.3 Security Requirements

Authentication: Multi-factor authentication (MFA) for sensitive operations
Authorization: Role-based access control (RBAC) with fine-grained permissions
Data Encryption:

At rest: AES-256 encryption
In transit: TLS 1.3
End-to-end encryption for sensitive documents


Privacy:

GDPR compliance for data protection
User consent management
Right to deletion and data portability
Anonymization for analytics


Security Testing:

Regular penetration testing
Vulnerability scanning
Security code reviews
Compliance audits



6.4 Performance Requirements

Response Time:

API response: < 200ms (95th percentile)
Page load: < 3 seconds on 3G
Search results: < 500ms


Throughput: Support 10,000 concurrent users initially, scalable to 100,000+
Availability: 99.5% uptime SLA
Data Sync: Offline changes sync within 30 seconds of reconnection
Storage:

500MB per farm for documents and media
5 years of historical data retention



6.5 Scalability Considerations

Horizontal scaling for all microservices
Database sharding for large datasets
CDN for static assets and media
Load balancing across multiple regions
Auto-scaling based on traffic patterns
Caching strategy for frequently accessed data


7. User Interface/User Experience (UI/UX)
7.1 Design Principles

Simplicity First: Prioritize ease of use over feature complexity
Visual Communication: Use icons, colors, and images to transcend language barriers
Offline-Ready: All core features must work without internet
Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum
Culturally Relevant: Localized imagery and examples
Progressive Disclosure: Show basic features first, advanced features on demand
Feedback-Rich: Clear confirmation and error messages for all actions

7.2 Key User Flows
7.2.1 Farmer Onboarding Flow

Download app or access web portal
Select preferred language
Choose role (Farmer) and farm type (Pig/Poultry/Both)
Register with phone number (OTP verification)
Complete farm profile (location, size, production system)
Take initial biosecurity risk assessment
Receive personalized dashboard and recommendations
Guided tour of key features

7.2.2 Risk Assessment Flow

Navigate to "Biosecurity Check" from dashboard
Select assessment type (Quick/Comprehensive)
Answer guided questions with:

Yes/No toggles
Image examples for clarity
Help tooltips for technical terms


View results with:

Overall risk score and rating
Domain-wise breakdown
Priority recommendations
Comparison with previous assessments


Save results and set reminder for next assessment

7.2.3 Alert Response Flow

Receive push notification about disease outbreak
Open app to alert details:

Disease type and severity
Distance from farm
Affected species
Map showing outbreak location


View recommended actions checklist
Mark actions as completed
Access related training modules
Share alert with farm staff/veterinarian

7.2.4 Compliance Tracking Flow

Navigate to "Compliance" section
View dashboard with:

Overall compliance percentage
Upcoming deadlines
Missing documents


Select specific requirement
Upload supporting documents (camera/gallery)
Mark requirement as completed
Receive confirmation and next steps
Generate compliance report for inspection

