17. Conclusion and Next Steps
17.1 Summary
The Digital Farm Management Portal for Biosecurity represents a comprehensive solution to address critical gaps in biosecurity knowledge, implementation, and compliance among pig and poultry farmers. By leveraging mobile-first technology, multilingual content, and user-centered design, the platform will democratize access to essential biosecurity tools and information, particularly for smallholder farmers in resource-limited settings.
The platform's success will be measured not just by user adoption metrics, but by tangible improvements in farm-level biosecurity practices, reduction in disease outbreak incidence, and enhanced livelihoods for farming families. Through strategic partnerships with government agencies, veterinary professionals, NGOs, and agribusinesses, the platform aims to create a collaborative ecosystem that strengthens the entire livestock value chain.
